docs.lead_paragraph: The charity, which raised $372 million in 2015, has embraced aggressive styles of fund-raising, marketing and management — and has spent a significant proportion on overhead.

headline.main: Wounded Warrior Project Spends Lavishly on Itself, Insiders Say
headline.print_headline: Helping Veterans Recover, Spending Lavishly on Itself

docs.abstract: Over four dozen current and former employees of Wounded Warrior Project, largest and fastest-growing veterans charity in country, say organization has spent lavishly on its employees, and on lobbying and public relations campaigns in effort to fight restrictions on amount charities can spend on overhead; project spent around 40 percent of $124 million in donations it received in 2014 on overhead.
docs.snippet: The charity, which raised $372 million in 2015, has embraced aggressive styles of fund-raising, marketing and management — and has spent a significant proportion on overhead.

headline.main: Oklahoma Resists Push for Enrollment in Affordable Care Act Coverage
headline.print_headline: Oklahoma Resists a Push for Enrollment in Affordable Care Act Coverage

docs.abstract: Health insurance advocates in Oklahoma are making last push to enroll uninsured before end of Affordable Care Act's third annual open enrollment, despite strong resistance in state that is one of most opposed to health law; nearly 600,000 Oklahoma residents are uninsured.
